==English==
===Etymology===
Modelled on '''[[dilemma]]''', replacing '''[[di-]]''', two with '''[[tri-]]''', three

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''trilemma''' (''plural:'' '''trilemmas''' or '''trilemmata''')

#A [[circumstance]] in which a [[choice]] must be made between [[three]] [[option]]s that seem equally [[undesirable]].
#{{logic}} A [[syllogism]] containing three [[alternative]]s that each infer the same [[conclusion]].
#('''the trilemma''') A form of [[apologetics]] meant to prove the divinity of Jesus.

